@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - computeinstanceagent/InstanceAgentPlugin
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired InstanceAgentPlugin spec, tracked\nstatus, and delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetInstanceAgentPlugin;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListInstanceAgentPlugins using filters\ncompartmentId, instanceagentId, pluginName;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path is not represented by imported\nprovider facts;
:Confirm deletion via GetInstanceAgentPlugin or\nListInstanceAgentPlugins until OCI reaches\nLOCAL_DELETE;
:Allow best-effort completion without finalizer\nretention;
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches RUNNING, STOPPED, NOT_SUPPORTED,\nINVALID;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartmentId, instanceagentId,\npluginName;
stop
endif
:Apply explicit follow-up semantics\ncreate=none; update=none; delete=none;
:Return success for the RUNNING, STOPPED,\nNOT_SUPPORTED, INVALID success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nnone;
:Requeue on terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: computeinstanceagent
slug: instanceagentplugin
kind: InstanceAgentPlugin
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required / none
requeue: terminating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
follow-up: create=none; update=none; delete=none
supported drift: none
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, instanceagentId, pluginName
create-only fields: none
list lookup:
oci_compute_instance_agent_instance_agent_plugins
filters compartmentId, instanceagentId,
pluginName; Direct reads require the exact
composite identity
instanceagentId+compartmentId+pluginName.
Confirmation-only list reads reuse the same
scope and treat an exact plugin-name match as
the bound plugin; unexpected surviving matches
fail instead of guessing.
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Compute Instance Agent exposes
GetInstanceAgentPlugin and
ListInstanceAgentPlugins only in the pinned SDK,
so the published runtime is bind-existing and
observe-only.
Bind identity is explicit: reconcile requires
compartmentId, instanceagentId, and pluginName,
tracks the composite identity in status, and
uses ListInstanceAgentPlugins only to confirm
absence after a reread no longer finds the
tracked plugin.
No OCI create, update, or delete operation is
published. Plugin enable or disable remains part
of Core UpdateInstance and is out of scope for
this package.
Visible plugin states RUNNING, STOPPED,
NOT_SUPPORTED, and INVALID are all stable
observed states. Delete is Kubernetes-local
unbind only and settles through best-effort
local cleanup rather than cloud-side terminal
waiting.
end note
@enduml
